    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.7.EE.B.4a</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Solve word problems leading to equations of the form &lt;i&gt;px&lt;/i&gt; + &lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt; = &lt;i&gt;r&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;x&lt;/i&gt; + &lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt;) = &lt;i&gt;r&lt;/i&gt;, where &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt;, and &lt;i&gt;r&lt;/i&gt; are specific rational numbers. Solve equations of these forms fluently. Compare an algebraic solution to an arithmetic solution, identifying the sequence of the operations used in each approach. &lt;i&gt;For example, the perimeter of a rectangle is 54 cm. Its length is 6 cm. What is its width?&lt;/i&gt;</Statement>
    </Statements>
    <GradeLevels>
      <GradeLevel>07</GradeLevel>
    </GradeLevels>
